article.headline: Drake 79, Bradley 73
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Pete Eggers scored 17 points as Drake beat Bradley 79-73 Saturday. Eggers led five Bulldogs who scored in double figures as Drake (5-7, 2-3 Missouri Valley) ended a two-game losing streak. Drake and Bradley were tied at 57 with 5:41 left to play when the Bulldogs went on an 11-3 run to take a 68-60 lead behind Kyle Korver's 3-pointer and two free throws. Drake sank 13-of-14 free throws down the stretch to clinch the win. Korver and Lonnie Randolph each finished with 12 points for Drake. Korver added a career-high 11 rebounds. Bradley (9-3, 2-2) was led by Tony Bennett, who scored 24 points. Jeremy Crouch added 17 points, including five 3-pointers, for Bradley.
